## Note on source material

The keywords, symbolism descriptions, and upright/reversed meanings in
`skill/tarot/cards.json` are modern Traditional Chinese rewrites by the
copyright holder, derived from the following public-domain sources:

- Arthur Edward Waite, *The Pictorial Key to the Tarot* (London: Rider & Co.,
  1910). Public domain worldwide.
- Rider-Waite-Smith tarot deck imagery (1909), illustrated by Pamela Colman
  Smith. Public domain in the United States since 1938, and in most other
  jurisdictions.

No content from any modern copyrighted tarot interpretation source
(e.g., Biddy Tarot) has been included.
